{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Some studies use the strong interpretative abilities of LLMs as agents to continuously improve data storage, data analysis, and additional areas [11], [21].",
    "For instance, the authors in [11] introduced GPT-4, which has demonstrated remarkable capabilities in understanding and generating humanlike text, facilitating various data management tasks [11].",
    "The authors in [22] presented an LLM-based database framework that leverages LLMs for automatic prompt generation and model fine-tuning, which performs highly effective in query rewriting and index tuning [22].",
    "In [23], the authors introduced Data-Copilot, which is a data analysis agent capable of autonomously querying, processing, and visualizing vast amounts of data to meet various human needs.",
    "Existing works mainly focus on unimodal LLMs processing text data, while relatively insufficient research has been done on the integration of multi-modal data such as text, images, and structured data."
  ],
